# Outreach generation_inputs Contract (Phase 2 traceability)

## Why

`outreach_queue.generation_inputs` (jsonb, added 2026-04-27) is how admins
answer **"why does this draft look the way it does?"** without re-running the
LLM. The "Why this draft?" popover (`components/admin/outreach/WhyThisDraftModal.tsx`)
and the "Preview prompt" affordance both read from this shape.

If a generator writes to `outreach_queue` without populating `generation_inputs`,
the row becomes a black box — admins see "Trace not recorded" and lose the
ability to audit, tweak, or compare.

## Where it lives

- DB column: `public.outreach_queue.generation_inputs` (`jsonb`, nullable)
- Migration: `migrations/2026_04_27_outreach_queue_generation_inputs.sql`
- Type: [`GenerationInputs`](../../lib/outreach-queue-generator.ts) in
  `lib/outreach-queue-generator.ts` — single source of truth for the shape
- Builder: `buildGenerationInputs({ ctx, templateKey, channel, sequenceStep })`
  in the same file — always use it; do **not** hand-roll the object literal
- Reader (existing draft): `GET /api/admin/outreach/drafts/:queueId/inputs`
- Reader (preview, no LLM call): `GET /api/admin/outreach/leads/:id/preview-prompt?channel=&templateKey=`

## Required keys (must all be set on insert)

```ts
{
  template_key: string                 // matches a row in system_prompts.key
  prompt_version: number | null        // system_prompts.version snapshot
  channel: 'email' | 'linkedin'
  model: string                        // resolved model id sent to the LLM
  provider: 'openai' | 'anthropic'     // inferProvider(model)
  temperature: number
  max_tokens: number
  sequence_step: number                // 1-6
  research_brief_chars: number
  social_proof_chars: number
  meeting_summary_present: boolean
  meeting_text_source: 'none' | 'inline_summary' | 'structured_summary' | 'raw_notes' | 'transcript_excerpt'
  meeting_action_items_chars: number
  pinecone_chars: number               // RAG block length, 0 when disabled
  prior_chat_present: boolean
  pinecone_block_hash: string | null   // sha256(8) of the RAG block, null when no block
  prior_outreach_chars: number
  prior_outreach_entries: number
  prior_outreach_has_inbound: boolean
  value_evidence_chars: number         // industry VEP excerpt injected into brief
  value_evidence_rows: number
  rag_query_chars: number
  rag_skipped_reason: string | null    // e.g. email_rag_disabled, n8n_outbound_disabled
  rag_attempted: boolean
  rag_error_class: string | null       // http | timeout | network | parse
  rag_http_status: number | null
  rag_latency_ms: number | null
  rag_empty_response: boolean         // HTTP ok but normalized block empty
}
```

Adding a new context block (e.g. Phase 3 `prior_outreach_history`)? Update the
`GenerationInputs` type, `buildGenerationInputs`, the migration's column comment,
and the WhyThisDraftModal `KvSection` rendering in lockstep.

## When to write

Every code path that inserts into `outreach_queue` with `status='draft'` and
the row was produced by an in-app generator must set `generation_inputs`.
Reuse `buildOutreachPromptContext` so the sizes / fingerprint come out
correctly — do not skip RAG just because tests are noisy. Use
`EMAIL_RAG_ENABLED=false` in tests instead.

Drafts produced manually (rep typed it themselves) or by external callbacks
that don't have the trace can leave `generation_inputs` `null`. The UI treats
`null` as "Trace not recorded" — that's the supported gap.

## Don'ts

- Don't store the full assembled prompt in `generation_inputs`. Use the
  `preview-prompt` route to re-derive on demand. Storing the prompt would
  bloat the table and leak Pinecone content.
- Don't widen `generation_inputs` to capture per-token usage — that's
  `llm_costs` territory, joined by `outreach_queue.id` when needed.
- Don't add a `CHECK` constraint on the jsonb shape. Phase 3 will append
  fields; a strict schema would force a coordinated migration every time.
- Don't expose `generation_inputs` to non-admin endpoints — it's an audit
  surface, not a customer-facing field.
